  <p>Dear Justin,</p>
  
  <p>You won't believe this but I've just sat through 'Titanic'. I&#xA0;<input id="q1"/>&#xA0;you and I swore we would never watch it but I really&#xA0;<input id="q2"/>&#xA0;you might be missing a great film if you&#xA0;<input id="q3"/>&#xA0;it!</p>
  
  <p>It's not just about the sinking of the ship - it's a romance and a disaster film rolled into one! It&#xA0;<input id="q4"/>&#xA0;in modern times and then the whole story&#xA0;<input id="q5"/>&#xA0;in flashbacks by Rose, a survivor of the tragedy. The main story is about how Rose, as a young woman,&#xA0;<input id="q6"/>&#xA0;from a suicide attempt by Jack, a passenger from the lower decks of the ship, and how they gradually&#xA0;<input id="q7"/>&#xA0;closer to each other. The plot is full of suspense and&#xA0;<input id="q8"/>&#xA0;you breathless in parts. You really can't help but get caught up in the emotions of their impossible situation and the tragedy that&#xA0;<input id="q9"/>, though there are a few corny moments! The two main stars and the supporting cast&#xA0;<input id="q10"/>&#xA0;excellent though. The costumes and the sets inside the ship are fabulous and really&#xA0;<input id="q11"/>&#xA0;the period to life.</p>
  
  <p>So do try and find a spare three hours or so and&#xA0;<input id="q12"/>&#xA0;and&#xA0;<input id="q13"/>&#xA0;it. I really do think you'll be pleasantly surprised!</p>
  
  <p>Looking forward to catching up on all your news.</p>
  <p>All the best,<br/>
	Maxine </p>
